  "body": "The implementation of each class' serialization/deserialization is no longer passed within a macro.\nThe implementation now lies within a template of form:\n\n```\ntemplate <typename Stream, typename Operation>\ninline size_t SerializationOp(Stream& s, Operation ser_action, int nType, int nVersion) {\n    /* CODE */\n}\n```\n\nIn cases when codepath should depend on whether or not we are just deserializing\n(old **fGetSize**, **fWrite**, **fRead** flags) an additional clause can be used:\n\n```\nbool fRead = ser_action.ForRead();\n```\n\nThe **IMPLEMENT_SERIALIZE** macro will now be a freestanding clause added within class' body\n(similiar to Qt's **Q_OBJECT**) to implement **GetSerializeSize**, **Serialize** and **Unserialize**.\nThese are now wrappers around the **SerializationOp** template.\n",
